lves for posterity casts fresh light on the actual processes that lead to literary fame.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aAuthors and readersxHistoryx19th centuryxEngland. 0aAuthors and readerszEnglandxHistoryy19th century. 0aAuthors, EnglishxAppreciationx19th century. 0aAuthors, Englishy19th centuryxAppreciation. 0aEnglish literaturexHistory and criticismx19th century. 0aEnglish literaturey19th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aFamexHistoryx19th century. 0aFamexHistoryy19th century. 0aInfluence (Literary, artistic, etc.)xHistoryx19th century. 0aInfluence (Literary, artistic, etc.)xHistoryy19th century. 0aReputationxHistoryx19th centuryxEngland. 0aReputationzEnglandxHistoryy19th century. 0aRomanticismxHistoryx19th centuryxEngland. 0aRomanticismzEnglandxHistoryy19th century. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Gothic & Romance.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311067250340uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030021330040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300213300423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300213300/original  a978-3-11-067250-3  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles